<ns1779:section xmlns:ns1779="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.tecnologies.java.j2se.java2D.java2DImageProcessing.java2DImageProcessing">
    
    <ns1780:title xmlns:ns1780="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java 2D Image Processing</ns1780:title>

<ns1781:para xmlns:ns1781="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java 2D has powerful support for image processing. It supports general 
convolutions, pixel manipulations via lookup tables, color conversions
    and affine transformations.</ns1781:para>
    <ns1782:figure xmlns:ns1782="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.tecnologies.java.j2se.java2D.java2DImageProcessing.java2DImageProcessing.imageConvolution_gif">
        <ns1783:title xmlns:ns1783="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ImageConvolution</ns1783:title>
      <mediaobject xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><imageobject><imagedata fileref="ImageConvolution.gif"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</ns1782:figure>
<ns1784:para xmlns:ns1784="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The original image is sharpened, blurred, inverted, sent through
           threshold and posterization filters.</ns1784:para>
<ns1785:para xmlns:ns1785="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
We demonstrate some of Java's image processing capability with a simple
application which applies some standard convolution (sharpening, blurring
edge detection) and table-lookup (inversion, thresholding, posterization)
operations on images.
</ns1785:para>
